				<wikidot:authorName>MathBrush</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2026461</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thanks so much to fieldstone, calamitous1 and Modern-Erasmus for their help and suggestions!</p> <p>The image is from Wikimedia Commons. The following information was provided there:</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>Foliage and fruit<br /> Rosenzweig - Self-photographed<br /> Fruit and leaves of a Wild Service Tree (Sorbus torminalis), photographed in Weinsberg</p> <p>own work<br /> CC BY-SA 3.0<br /> Created: 29 September 2007</p> </blockquote> <p>The CC BY-SA 3.0 license can be read here: <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/">https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/</a></p> </div> </div> </div> <p>My goal with this entry was to show how something that we generally regard as amusing in movies or cartoons would have horrible consequences in real life.</p> <p>I hope you enjoy my flatulence-based entry!</p> 
				 	]]>
